**What parser (default, Babel-ESLint, etc.) are you using?**
default

**Please show your full configuration:**
N/A

**What did you do? Please include the actual source code causing the issue, as well as the command that you used to run ESLint.**
Ran the code provided in the [messageId](https://eslint.org/docs/developer-guide/working-with-rules#messageids) section of the Working with Rules page.
Recreated below: 

<!-- Paste the source code below: -->
lib/rules/no-foo.js
```js
'use strict';
module.exports = {
    meta: {
        messages: {
            avoidName: "Avoid using variables named '{{ name }}'"
        }
    },
    create(context) {
        return {
            Identifier(node) {
                if (node.name === "foo") {
                    context.report({
                        node,
                        messageId: "avoidName",
                        data: {
                            name: "foo",
                        }
                    });
                }
            }
        };
    }
};
```


tests/lib/rules/no-foo.js
*Updated require path which was `var rule = require('../../../lib/rules/no-insecure-random');` which seems unrelated to this example.*
```js
'use strict';
// In your tests:
var rule = require('../../../lib/rules/no-foo');
var RuleTester = require('eslint').RuleTester;

var ruleTester = new RuleTester();
ruleTester.run('my-rule', rule, {
  valid: ['bar', 'baz'],

  invalid: [
    {
      code: 'foo',
      errors: [
        {
          messageId: 'foo',
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
});
```

